<TITLE> Ex-mayor, Rajshahi runner Minu out on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)  Former mayor of Rajshahi City Corporation and BNP's central organising secretary Mizanur Rahman Minu was freed on bail Sunday evening. "The papers for Minu's release came to the prison at 4:30pm and he was released at 6:35pm Sunday," said Harun-ur-Rashid, senior jail super of Rajshahi prison. The HC most recently granted him bail in two cases lodged by the Anticorruption Commission  for pilfering relief materials and irregularity in the allotment of shops in Rajshahi City Corporation. In all, Minu has secured bail in five of six cases that had been filed against himincluding an extortion case in which he and 11 others were sentenced in August last year to 13 years each. Police dropped charges in the sixth, which accused the BNP leader of backing extremists. Minu was released once before on bail, on Jun. 10 last year, but re-arrested the next day under Emergency Powers Rules and detained in Rajshahi Central Jail until his release. The former mayor has received the BNP ticket to run from Rajshahi-2. bdnews24.com/c
